# UI & E2E (HalalScan)

Full guide: [TESTING.md](../../TESTING.md) (local Supabase, barcodes, coverage registry).

## When this rule applies

Navigation, scan flow, result screen, shared widgets used on those flows, `integration_test/`, or stable test keys in `lib/integration_test_keys.dart`.

## E2E registry (keep in sync)

After behavior-visible UI changes, update **together**:

1. [`test/e2e_coverage.json`](../../test/e2e_coverage.json)
2. [`test/barcodes_e2e.txt`](../../test/barcodes_e2e.txt)
3. [`lib/integration_test_keys.dart`](../../lib/integration_test_keys.dart)

Then:

```bash
./scripts/validate_e2e_coverage.sh    # also: flutter test test/constants/
./scripts/preview_e2e_coverage.sh     # optional: read registry
```

## Run on device when behavior changed

Local stack + UI E2E (not widget mocks):

```powershell
.\scripts\start_e2e_supabase.ps1
.\run_ui_e2e_test.ps1                 # dart_defines.e2e.json — never dart_defines.json
```

```bash
./scripts/start_e2e_supabase.sh
./run_ui_e2e_test.sh
```

See [TESTING.md → Local Supabase for E2E](../../TESTING.md#local-supabase-for-e2e).

## CI unit tests still required

UI work does not replace:

```bash
flutter test test/services/ test/constants/ test/models/ test/config_test.dart
```
